
ffmpeg -framerate 30 -pattern_type glob -i "frames/*.bmp" -c:v libx264 -crf 17 -pix_fmt yuv420p my-timelapse.mp4

ffprobe -show_format my-timelapse.mp4
^^ to get exact duration for fade out, subtract the duration of fadeout from the end time

ffmpeg -i my-timelapse.mp4 -filter:v "fade=t=in:st=0:d=1,fade=t=out:st=12.467:d=1" timelapse.mp4
^^ fading

use levell.scm ~/.config/GIMP/2.10/scripts to change the levels, contrasts, etc
